    slug: "minhaj-ul-muslim-english-2-vols",
    description: `Minhaj ul Muslim English (2 volumes) is a comprehensive two-volume English translation of the celebrated Islamic reference work originally authored by the renowned scholar Abu Bakr Jabir al-Jaza'iri. This monumental work serves as a complete guide to the daily life, worship, conduct, and spiritual development of a practising Muslim, covering virtually every aspect of Islamic practice from the five pillars of faith to the finer details of personal etiquette and social interaction. The original Arabic text of Minhaj ul Muslim has long been regarded as one of the most thorough and well-organised fiqh (Islamic jurisprudence) reference books available to the Muslim community, and this English translation makes its invaluable content accessible to English-speaking Muslims who seek a reliable, detailed manual for living their lives in accordance with the teachings of Islam. The first volume is dedicated to the foundational acts of worship, beginning with a detailed treatment of the declaration of faith (shahadah) and its implications for belief and practice, followed by an extensive and meticulous explanation of the ritual prayer (salah) that covers purification (wudu and ghusl), the conditions and prerequisites of prayer, the pillars and obligations of each unit of prayer, the recommended supplications, the prayer of the traveller, the Friday congregational prayer, the Eid prayers, the funeral prayer, and the voluntary prayers. The section on fasting (siyam) provides comprehensive guidance on the rulings of Ramadan fasting, voluntary fasting, and expiatory fasting. The chapter on zakah (obligatory charity) explains the types of wealth subject to zakah, the calculation methods, and the categories of eligible recipients. The volume on Hajj covers the entire pilgrimage journey from the ihram to the farewell tawaf, including all the rites of Mina, Arafat, and Muzdalifah. The second volume addresses the broader dimensions of a Muslim's life, including the Islamic etiquettes of eating, drinking, sleeping, dressing, entering and leaving the home, greeting others, visiting the sick, attending funerals, and conducting business transactions. The book also covers marriage and family life, divorce, inheritance, and the Islamic ethics of speech, friendship, and neighbourly relations. Each ruling is supported by references to the Quran and the authentic hadith of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), and the presentation follows a clear, logical structure that makes it easy to locate specific guidance. This two-volume set is an indispensable reference for Muslim households, Islamic schools, and anyone seeking a thorough and trustworthy guide to Islamic practice.`,
