    slug: "mukhtasar-bayan-ul-quran-by-dr-israr-ahmed",
    description: `Mukhtasar Bayan ul Quran by Dr Israr Ahmed is a concise Urdu summary and thematic commentary of the Holy Quran, compiled from the extensive lecture series and written works of the distinguished Islamic scholar and thinker Dr Israr Ahmed (1932–2010), who was one of the most influential Islamic voices in the Urdu-speaking world during the twentieth century. Dr Israr Ahmed devoted decades to the study and teaching of the Quran, and his magnum opus, the complete Bayan ul Quran, is a multi-volume tafsir (Quranic exegesis) that covers the entire Quran in a distinctive style that combines scholarly depth with accessible language and a powerful emphasis on the Quran's message of social justice, spiritual revival, and the establishment of a just Islamic order. This Mukhtasar (concise/abridged) edition distils the essential themes and core messages of each surah into a compact and manageable format, making the profound insights of Dr Israr Ahmed's Quranic commentary available to a wider audience who may not have the time or opportunity to engage with the complete multi-volume work. The book follows the order of the Quranic surahs, providing for each surah a summary of its historical context (asbab al-nuzul), its central themes, its key verses and their significance, and the practical lessons that Dr Israr Ahmed drew from his deep engagement with the text. A distinctive feature of Dr Israr Ahmed's approach is his emphasis on the Quran as a dynamic and revolutionary text that calls for the transformation of both individual character and collective social structures, and this emphasis is reflected throughout the concise commentary. The book highlights the Quran's message of tawheed (the oneness of God), its critique of social inequality and economic exploitation, its vision of a just and equitable society governed by divine guidance, and its urgent call to the Muslim community to rise above complacency and fulfil its responsibility as witnesses to humanity. The commentary also addresses the spiritual dimensions of the Quran, including its teachings on the purification of the soul, the cultivation of inner virtues, the reality of the Hereafter, and the relationship between human beings and their Creator. Written in Dr Israr Ahmed's characteristic Urdu prose style — which is clear, persuasive, and deeply informed by both classical Islamic scholarship and contemporary social analysis — this concise Quranic summary is an invaluable resource for anyone who wishes to gain a comprehensive understanding of the Quran's message in a single, accessible volume.`,
    metaDescription: "Mukhtasar Bayan ul Quran by Dr Israr Ahmed is a concise Urdu thematic summary and commentary of the entire Quran from his renowned lecture series."
