    slug: "mukhtasar-riyad-us-saliheen-urdu",
    description: `Mukhtasar Riyad us Saliheen Urdu is a condensed Urdu translation and abridgement of the celebrated hadith collection Riyad us Saliheen (The Gardens of the Righteous), originally compiled by the eminent hadith scholar Imam Yahya ibn Sharaf an-Nawawi (631–676 AH / 1233–1277 CE). Imam Nawawi's Riyad us Saliheen is widely considered one of the most popular and beneficial collections of Prophetic traditions ever assembled, and it has been a staple of Muslim households, mosques, and educational institutions for over seven centuries. The work gathers approximately two thousand authentic hadith narrations organised into thematic chapters that cover every significant aspect of a Muslim's life — from belief and worship to ethics, social relations, and personal development — making it a practical and comprehensive guide to living according to the Sunnah of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him). This Mukhtasar (concise) Urdu edition carefully selects the most essential and frequently referenced narrations from the complete collection, presenting them in clear, contemporary Urdu that is accessible to readers of all educational backgrounds. The thematic organisation is preserved, allowing readers to easily locate hadith related to specific topics such as sincerity, patience, gratitude, modesty, kindness to parents, charity, fasting, pilgrimage, seeking knowledge, dealing with neighbours, visiting the sick, the rights of spouses, the etiquettes of eating and drinking, the virtues of various acts of worship, the remembrance of Allah, supplications for different occasions, and warnings against major sins. Each hadith is presented with its full chain of narrators (isnad) where applicable, along with the degree of its authenticity as assessed by the hadith scholars. The Urdu translation is faithful to the original Arabic while remaining fluid and natural, and brief explanatory notes are provided where the context or meaning of a narration requires clarification. The concise nature of this edition makes it particularly suitable for daily reading and reference, allowing busy individuals to benefit from the wisdom of the Prophetic traditions without the commitment required by the complete multi-volume collection. It is an ideal companion for family circles, study groups, and personal spiritual development, and it serves as an excellent introduction to the hadith literature for students who are beginning their journey into the science of Prophetic traditions. This edition upholds the scholarly standards that have made Riyad us Saliheen one of the most trusted hadith collections in the Islamic world, while making its treasures accessible to the Urdu-speaking community in a convenient and practical format.`,
