    slug: "mukhtasar-sahih-al-bukhari-2-vols-imported",
    description: `Mukhtasar Sahih al-Bukhari (2 volumes) is an imported two-volume Urdu abridgement of Sahih al-Bukhari, the most authoritative and revered collection of hadith in the entire Islamic tradition, compiled by the great Imam Muhammad ibn Ismail al-Bukhari (194–256 AH / 810–870 CE). Imam al-Bukhari devoted sixteen years to the compilation of this monumental work, selecting approximately seven thousand three hundred and ninety-seven hadith narrations from a pool of over six hundred thousand that he examined, applying the most rigorous criteria of authenticity ever established in the science of hadith. The result is a work that the Muslim community has unanimously regarded as the most authentic book after the Holy Quran, a distinction that has remained unchallenged for over twelve centuries. This Mukhtasar (abridged) edition distils the essential content of the complete Sahih al-Bukhari into two manageable volumes, carefully preserving the most important narrations while making the work more accessible to general readers who may find the complete collection's extensive detail and scholarly apparatus challenging. The hadith narrations in this abridgement are organised into thematic chapters that cover the full range of Islamic knowledge and practice, beginning with the book of revelation and the book of faith, proceeding through the books of purification, prayer, zakah, fasting, pilgrimage, and jihad, and extending to the books of marriage, divorce, trade, inheritance, medicine, manners, virtues, and the signs of the Last Day. Each chapter heading provides the original Arabic title as used by Imam al-Bukhari, and the hadith narrations are presented with their chains of narrators and the full Arabic text, accompanied by the Urdu translation. The two-volume format allows the content to be divided into logical sections, with the first volume generally covering the acts of worship and the second volume addressing social transactions, ethics, and eschatology. The imported edition features high-quality printing on durable paper with clear, legible Arabic typography and well-formatted Urdu text, reflecting the production standards of established Islamic publishing houses. Brief explanatory footnotes are included where the meaning of a narration requires additional context or clarification. This abridged Sahih al-Bukhari is an essential addition to every Muslim household library, serving both as a reference work for scholars and students and as a source of spiritual nourishment for general readers who wish to connect with the authentic words and teachings of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) through the most reliable transmission chain in Islamic history.`,
