    slug: "mukhtaser-riyad-us-saliheen-urdu",
    description: `Mukhtaser Riyad us Saliheen Urdu is a carefully prepared Urdu summary and abridgement of the famous hadith compilation Riyad us Saliheen (Gardens of the Righteous) by Imam Yahya ibn Sharaf an-Nawawi, one of the most widely read and cherished collections of Prophetic traditions in the Islamic world. This edition serves as a companion volume to the more detailed Mukhtasar edition, offering an even more streamlined presentation of Imam Nawawi's carefully curated selection of authentic hadith narrations that together form a comprehensive guide to Islamic life, ethics, and spirituality. Imam Nawawi organised his collection into chapters that correspond to the practical concerns of a Muslim's daily existence, grouping together narrations that address related themes such as the virtues of various good deeds, the importance of sincerity in worship, the etiquette of social interaction, the rights of parents and children, the duties of spouses, the ethics of business and trade, the rules of fasting and prayer, the manners of eating and drinking, the importance of seeking knowledge, the warnings against major sins, the descriptions of Paradise and Hell, and the recommended supplications for every conceivable occasion. This Mukhtaser (more concise) Urdu edition further distils the content by focusing on the most impactful and frequently referenced narrations from each chapter, presenting them in clear, flowing Urdu that captures the essence and beauty of the original Arabic text. Each hadith is accompanied by its reference number in the complete Riyad us Saliheen, allowing readers who wish to explore a narration in greater detail to locate it in the full edition. The Urdu translation has been crafted to be faithful to the meaning of the Arabic while remaining accessible to readers who may not have advanced knowledge of Islamic terminology. Brief contextual notes are included where the historical background or technical meaning of a narration requires explanation for proper understanding. The compact format of this edition makes it particularly suitable for daily reading and reflection, for carrying during travel, for use in study circles and family gatherings, and for gifting to new Muslims and young people who are beginning their journey into the Prophetic traditions. The book is produced with attention to quality, featuring durable binding, clear printing, and a layout that makes it easy to find specific narrations and topics. This Mukhtaser edition ensures that the profound spiritual and practical guidance contained in Riyad us Saliheen remains accessible to the widest possible audience of Urdu-speaking Muslims.`,
